issue.title: All cache is refreshed on reorder of items in a structure
issue.body:
Hi,

Awesome plugin! Very happy with it. I have a little issue I'd like some help with: I have a structure with 50+ entries. When I change/update something in one of these entries, the blitz cache is updated beautifully for that page and all pages it has been referenced in. But, when I reorder one of these, let's say I drag the 2nd one to the 3rd place.. all cache is being updated. Which is very heavy on my server, so you can imagine I'd like to fix this.. ;-)

FYI, my refresh mode is set to **Clear the cache and regenerate in a queue job**

Thanks in advance!!

comment.body: If the order of a structure changes then _every_ entry in that structure can potentially have its order changed. Blitz is being cautious and refreshing every page that the reorder could potentially affect. But if that’s an issue, you have the config setting available to disable the behaviour.
